Morocco’s royal palace has issued a picture of King Mohammed VI visiting Gabon’s President Ali Bongo at hospital in Rabat where the Gabonese leader is recovering from an undisclosed illness. The publication of the photo comes after persistent rumours over the health of the Gabonese president for more than a month. Mr Bongo was flown to Morocco on Thursday from Saudi Arabia where he had been in hospital since 24 October after falling ill at an economic forum. Six Gabon papers suspended for ‘lack of ethics’ GABON: President Bongo ‘seriously ill but recovering’ Embarrassing spat